Not sure how the code works, but wouldn't it be better for the program to ignore that line of code when blockpause = 0?
I'm thinking this should help, unless the program has to go through this extra _if_ statement every time and not just once.

```
    if (Params().NetworkIDString() != "regtest" and blockpause != 0)
    {
        std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(blockpause));
    }
```

